nickname_garnet.description: Enters the nickname 'GARNET', first navigating to DEL to clear any accidental input. Assumes cursor starts at 'A'.
nickname_garnet.python_script:
import json
cmds = []

# Navigate to DEL from A (assumed start) to clear any accidental input
# Path: Down x4 -> lower. Right -> DEL.
cmds.extend(["Down"]*4)
cmds.append("Right")
cmds.append("A")
cmds.append("sleep 200")

# Navigate back to A from DEL
# Path: Left -> lower. Up x4 -> A.
cmds.append("Left")
cmds.extend(["Up"]*4)
cmds.append("sleep 200")

# Now enter GARNET
# G (0,6) from A(0,0)
cmds.extend(["Right"]*6)
cmds.append("A")
cmds.append("sleep 200")
# A (0,0) from G(0,6)
cmds.extend(["Left"]*6)
cmds.append("A")
cmds.append("sleep 200")
# R (1,8) from A(0,0)
cmds.append("Down")
cmds.extend(["Right"]*8)
cmds.append("A")
cmds.append("sleep 200")
# N (1,4) from R(1,8)
cmds.extend(["Left"]*4)
cmds.append("A")
cmds.append("sleep 200")
# E (0,4) from N(1,4)
cmds.append("Up")
cmds.append("A")
cmds.append("sleep 200")
# T (2,1) from E(0,4)
cmds.append("Down")
cmds.append("Down")
cmds.extend(["Left"]*3)
cmds.append("A")
cmds.append("sleep 200")
# END via Start
cmds.append("Start")
cmds.append("sleep 200")
cmds.append("A")

print(json.dumps(cmds))

history.commit_message: Adding cleanup step to remove accidental input before entering name.
